FBIS3-37229 "drsov031_a_94035" FBIS-SOV-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS `ITAR-TASS U.S.A.' Begins Operations LD1402225994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1308 GMT 14 Feb 94 LD1402225994 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Kolesnichenko] [Text] New York February 14 TASS--The Russian-American corporation ITAR-TASS U.S.A. started functioning in the United States. Its main tasks include the spreading in the North American Free Trade Zone of complete and reliable first-hand information about the developments in the political, economic and cultural life of Russia and other CIS member states and the promoting of contacts between political, business and academic circles of the two countries. The corporation was founded by the ITAR-TASS, the central news agency of Russia, and the U.S. company Kassengen Associates, which is actively operating on the CIS market. ITAR-TASS will supply subscribers as promptly as possible with various materials, including texts of presidential decrees, government resolutions, daily reports, analytical materials, business information bulletins and news about science, culture and sports. In its turn, Kassengen Associates, which has much experience in dealing with local business people, will help with the marketing of information products of the news agency. [Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian at 1330 GMT on 14 February provides the following contact telephone numbers for ITAR-TASS U.S.A.: New York--(212) 245-4250; Los Angeles--(800) 678-0616; and Moscow--(095) 229-64-03]
